  "text": "Sustainability assessments are measured through the definition of proposed aspects and indicators. Sustainable indicators have specific characteristics which come into consideration when designing a framework for assessing sustainability: measurable (quantitatively and/or qualitatively), relevant, understandable, and reliable [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A procedure to assess the dimensions of sustainability is introduced and used in assessing the strengths and weaknesses of the SMEs. The triple bottom line (TBL) is used to identify the intersection between pillars of sustainability ( Fig.  1) , suggesting that the intersection between sustainability pillars is not strong enough and needs more explanation to ensure the meaning of this value. Figure 2 illustrates the strong relationship between sustainability pillars not only in interactions but also in incorporation. This means that economic sustainability is the core Sustainability/sustainabl e development index (SDI) aspect of sustainability, followed by society and environment.",
